re/types.ts)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## BUILD ENGINE (src/core/engine.ts)\n\nFull implementation: 117 lines\n\nKey methods:\n- **constructor(config: SiteConfig)** - Initialize with site config\n- **registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin)** - Add plugin to pipeline\n- **registerTemplate(template: Template)** - Add template renderer\n- **resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]** - Topological sort with circular dependency detection\n- **async build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>** - Main build pipeline:\n  1. Calls beforeBuild hooks in dependency order\n  2. Calls transformContent hooks on each file in order (all files, all plugins)\n  3. Renders templates for each file\n  4. Calls afterBuild hooks in dependency order\n- **getPlugins(): Plugin[]** - Return registered plugins\n- **getTemplates(): Map<string, Template>** - Return templates\n\nError handling:\n- Throws \"Circular dependency detected: {name}\"\n- Throws \"Missing dependency: {name} requires {dep}\"\n\n---\n\n## TEMPLATES (src/core/templates.ts)\n\n**createDefaultTemplate()**: Article template with title, time, and content\n- Wraps content in `<article>` with `<h1>`, optional `<time>`, and `<div class=\"content\">`\n\n**createListTemplate()**: List template\n- Wraps content in `<h1>` and `<div class=\"list\">`\n\n---\n\n## CORE TESTS (tests/core.test.ts) - 15 TESTS\n\nAll tests MUST continue to pass:\n\n1. **registers plugins** - engine.registerPlugin() and getPlugins()\n2. **registers templates** - engine.registerTemplate() and getTemplates()\n3. **builds with default template and renders HTML** - HTML output contains DOCTYPE, title, content, siteTitle\n4. **builds with list template and renders list HTML** - Uses 'list' template, wraps content in div.list\n5. **outputs raw content when no matching template** - Falls back to raw content\n6. **calls plugin beforeBuild hook** - Invokes beforeBuild if present\n7. **calls plugin transformContent hook to transform files** - Files transformed through hook\n8. **calls plugin afterBuild hook** - Invokes afterBuild if present\n9. **executes plugins in dependency order** - Topological sort: a before b if b depends on a\n10. **throws on circular dependency** - Rejects circular graphs\n11. **throws on missing dependency** - Rejects unmet dependencies\n12. **applies multiple plugins transformContent in order** - Chains all transformContent hooks\n13. **provides shared data store in build context** - ctx.data available in hooks\n14. **retains file metadata through build** - metadata, date, tags preserved\n15. **produces empty output for empty file list** - Handles edge case\n\n---\n\n## PLUGIN TEST FILES - 60 TESTS TOTAL\n\n### Plugin 1: markdown-ext (8 tests)\n**File**: `/workspace/tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts`\n\nExpected factory: `createMarkdownExtPlugin()`\n\nTests:\n1. Converts basic markdown to HTML (`# Hello` → `<h1>Hello</h1>`, `**bold**` → `<strong>bold</strong>`)\n2. Handles footnotes with `[^1]` syntax → `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n3. Renders footnote section at bottom with `<section class=\"footnotes\">` and `<li id=\"fn-N\">`\n4. Converts `:::note\\n...\\n:::` container to `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">`\n5. Converts `:::warning\\n...\\n:::` to `<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\">`\n6. Converts `:::tip\\n...\\n:::` to `<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">`\n7. Preserves existing HTML in content\n8. Handles empty content\n\n**Key behaviors**:\n- Uses `marked` library for markdown → HTML conversion\n- Implements footnote parser: extracts `[^N]: text` definitions, replaces `[^N]` with superscript links\n- Implements admonition parser: converts `:::type\\nContent\\n:::` blocks to divs\n- transformContent hook only\n\n---\n\n### Plugin 2: asset-pipeline (9 tests)\n**File**: `/workspace/tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts`\n\nExpected factory: `createAssetPipelinePlugin()`\n\nTests:\n1. Rewrites relative image URLs: `src=\"./image.png\"` → `src=\"/assets/image.png\"`\n2. Rewrites relative link URLs: `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` → `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`\n3. Leaves absolute URLs unchanged: `https://cdn.com/...` untouched\n4. Generates asset manifest in `ctx.data['asset-manifest']` with `{assets: string[]}`\n5. Handles files with no asset references\n6. Handles multiple assets in one file\n7. Asset manifest includes all discovered assets across all files\n8. Does not double-process already-rewritten URLs (skip `/assets/...`)\n9. Manifest accumulates across multiple files\n\n**Key behaviors**:\n- transformContent hook\n- Regex patterns for `src=\"` and `href=\"` attributes\n- Tracks assets in `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` (created on first use)\n- Only rewrites relative paths (starting with `./` or `../` or just filename)\n- Accumulates manifest across all files processed\n\n---\n\n### Plugin 3: syntax-highlight (8 tests)\n**File**: `/workspace/tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts`\n\nExpected factory: `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()`\n\nTests:\n1. Adds language class to code blocks: `class=\"language-javascript\"` → `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"`\n2. Adds `data-language` attribute to `<pre>` tags: `<pre data-language=\"python\">`\n3. Handles multiple code blocks in one file\n4. Handles code blocks with no language specified (no changes)\n5. Adds `highlighted` class to processed blocks\n6. Preserves code block content\n7. Handles empty code blocks\n8. Does not modify inline `<code>` (only `<pre><code>`)\n\n**Key behaviors**:\n- transformContent hook\n- Pattern: `<pre><code class=\"language-LANG\">...` where LANG is captured\n- Rewrites to: `<pre data-language=\"LANG\"><code class=\"language-LANG highlighted\">...`\n- Only touches `<pre><code>` pairs with `class=\"language-*\"`\n- Leaves plain `<code>` untouched\n\n---\n\n### Plugin 4: taxonomy (8 tests)\n**File**: `/workspace/tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts`\n\nExpected factory: `createTaxonomyPlugin()`\n\nTests:\n1. Builds tag index from file tags: `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']` = `Map<string, ContentFile[]>`\n2. Generates tag listing pages in `ctx.output`: `tags/{tag}.html`\n3. Handles files with no tags\n4. Handles files with multiple tags\n5. Tag pages list all files with that tag\n6. Stores tag map in `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']`\n7. Handles empty file list\n8. Tags case-normalized to lowercase: `JavaScript` + `JAVASCRIPT` → both map to `javascript`\n\n**Key behaviors**:\n- beforeBuild + afterBuild hooks\n- beforeBuild: builds `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` from `file.tags`, stores in `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']`\n- afterBuild: generates HTML for each tag with list of posts\n- Tag names case-folded to lowercase\n- Files without tags are ignored\n- Output files at `tags/{tag}.html` containing list of matching files\n\n---\n\n### Plugin 5: rss-feed (9 tests)\n**File**: `/workspace/tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts`\n\nExpected factory: `createRssFeedPlugin()`\n\n**Dependencies**: `['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy']`\n\nTests:\n1. Generates valid RSS 2.0 XML: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>`, `</rss>`\n2. Feed items contain HTML content (from file.content), wrapped in `<![CDATA[...]]>`\n3. Feed items include category tags from taxonomy: `<category>{tag}</category>`\n4. Feed includes channel title from config: `<title>Test Site</title>`\n5. Feed items sorted by date newest first (using file.date)\n6. Handles files without dates (no `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>`)\n7. Feed link uses baseUrl from config: `<link>https://example.com</link>` and `<link>https://example.com/{slug}.html</link>`\n8. (implied) All posts included in feed\n9. (implied) Feed output at `feed.xml`\n\n**Key behaviors**:\n- afterBuild hook only\n- Reads files from `ctx.files`\n- Reads tags from `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']` (Map<string, ContentFile[]>)\n- Generates RSS 2.0 XML structure\n- Items sorted descending by date\n- Content wrapped in CDATA\n- Output to `ctx.output['feed.xml']`\n\n---\n\n### Plugin 6: search-index (8 tests)\n**File**: `/workspace/tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts`\n\nExpected factory: `createSearchIndexPlugin()`\n\n**Dependencies**: `['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight']`\n\nTests:\n1. Generates `search-index.json` in `ctx.output`\n2. Index entries have title, slug, and plain text content\n3. HTML tags stripped from indexed content: `<h1>Title</h1><p>text</p>` → `Title text`\n4. Code blocks included in searchable text: `<pre><code>const x = 1;</code></pre>` → `const x = 1;`\n5. Handles empty file list: returns `[]`\n6. Search index is valid JSON (parseable)\n7. Index is array with correct length\n8. Index entries include tags if present\n\n**Key behaviors**:\n- afterBuild hook only\n- Output format: JSON array of objects with {slug, title, content, tags?}\n- HTML stripper: removes all `<...>` tags to get plain text\n- Code blocks preserved (text content extracted)\n- Handles optional tags field\n- Output to `ctx.output['search-index.json']`\n\n---\n\n### Plugin 7: sitemap (8 tests)\n**File**: `/workspace/tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts`\n\nExpected factory: `createSitemapPlugin()`\n\n**Dependencies**: `['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']`\n\nTests:\n1. Generates `sitemap.xml` in `ctx.output`\n2. Includes all content page URLs from `ctx.output` keys: `post-1.html` → `https://example.com/post-1.html`\n3. Includes taxonomy tag page URLs: `tags/javascript.html` → `https://example.com/tags/javascript.html`\n4. Includes `feed.xml` URL if present\n5. URLs use baseUrl from config\n6. Sitemap is valid XML structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"`, `<urlset>`, `</urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>`\n7. Handles site with no tag pages\n8. (implied) All HTML files in output included\n\n**Key behaviors**:\n- afterBuild hook only\n- Reads `ctx.output` keys to build URL list\n- Reads `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']` to include tag page URLs\n- Checks for `feed.xml` in output\n- Generates XML sitemap with structure:\n  ```xml\n  <?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n  <urlset xmlns=\"...\">\n    <url><loc>...</loc></url>\n    ...\n  </urlset>\n  ```\n- Output to `ctx.output['sitemap.xml']`\n\n---\n\n### Plugin 8: dev-server (7 tests)\n**File**: `/workspace/tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts`\n\nExpected factory: `createDevServerPlugin()`\n\n**Dependencies**: `['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']`\n\nTests:\n1. Stores `dev-server-config` in `ctx.data`\n2. Config includes `port: number` (default 3000)\n3. Config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline: `assetPaths: string[]` and routes with `handler: 'asset'`\n4. Config includes search index path: `searchIndexPath: '/search-index.json'`\n5. Config includes content routes: routes with `handler: 'static'` for each HTML file\n6. Default port is 3000\n7. Handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully (empty assetPaths)\n\n**Key behaviors**:\n- afterBuild hook only\n- DevServerConfig interface:\n  ```typescript\n  {\n    port: number;\n    routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n    assetPaths: string[];\n    searchIndexPath: string;\n  }\n  ```\n- Port default: 3000\n- Reads `ctx.data['asset-manifest']` if available → extract assets → create routes\n- Reads `ctx.output` keys → create 'static' routes for .html files\n- Checks `ctx.output['search-index.json']` → set searchIndexPath\n- Output to `ctx.data['dev-server-config']`\n\n---\n\n## IMPLEMENTATION STRATEGY\n\n### Wave 1 (No dependencies)\n1. **markdown-ext** - Use `marked` library (in dependencies)\n2. **asset-pipeline** - URL rewriting with regex\n3. **syntax-highlight** - HTML manipulation for code blocks\n4. **taxonomy** - Tag aggregation and page generation\n\n### Wave 2 (Depend on Wave 1)\n5. **rss-feed** - XML generation, depends on markdown-ext and taxonomy\n6. **search-index** - JSON generation, depends on markdown-ext and syntax-highlight\n\n### Wave 3 (Depend on Wave 2)\n7. **sitemap** - XML generation, depends on taxonomy and rss-feed\n8. **dev-server** - Config generation, depends on asset-pipeline and search-index\n\n---\n\n## KEY PATTERNS TO IMPLEMENT\n\n**Plugin Factory Pattern**:\n```typescript\nexport function createXxxPlugin(): Plugin {\n  return {\n    name: 'xxx',\n    version: '1.0.0',\n    dependencies: [],\n    hooks: {\n      beforeBuild?: async (ctx) => {...},\n      transformContent?: async (file, ctx) => {...},\n      afterBuild?: async (ctx) => {...},\n    }\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Data Storage**: Use `ctx.data.get()/set()` for inter-plugin communication\n- `taxonomy-tags`: Map<string, ContentFile[]>\n- `asset-manifest`: {assets: string[]}\n- `dev-server-config`: DevServerConfig object\n\n**Output Generation**: Use `ctx.output.set(path, content)` for generated files\n\n**File Transformation**: Return modified ContentFile from transformContent hooks\n\n---\n\n## EXPORT PATTERN (src/plugins/index.ts - needed)\nEach plugin file should export its factory function and be re-exported from a central index:\n```typescript\nexport { createMarkdownExtPlugin } from './markdown-ext.js';\nexport { createAssetPipelinePlugin } from './asset-pipeline.js';\n// ... etc\n```\n\n---\n\nThis is the complete picture. All 8 plugins must implement the Plugin interface, follow the specified dependencies, and pass the 60 tests while maintaining all 15 core engine tests."}],"totalDurationMs":55753,"totalTokens":38845,"totalToolUseCount":22,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":140,"cache_read_input_tokens":33504,"output_tokens":5199,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":140,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[]}}}
